        "timestamp": "2021-05-19 12:58:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nI understand where this 'var' comes from; C++. In C++ type names can be extremely complex and hard to read when templates are used. \n\nBut in this case when replacing simple type names like \n'int' to 'var' is not an improvement (it is making the code less readable since you have to figure out the type yourself when reading).",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "7c07b35b067fc05793d0649507792d6da3312edb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3763,
